TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Lookup Sql Override
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: select aa.CASINOLOCDETID as CASINOLOCDETID, substring(aa.CASINOLOC,1,6) as CASINOLOC, aa.TBLAREA as TBLAREA, aa.SiteID as SiteID from ( SELECT D_CASINOLOCATIONDET.CASINOLOCDETID, case when loctypcode= 'T' then 1 when loctypcode= 'S' then 1 when loctypcode= 'B' then 2 when loctypcode= 'C' then 2 when loctypcode='F' then 2 when loctypcode= 'O' then 2 when loctypcode='R' then 2 when loctypcode='U' then 9 else 5 end as SctyCde, D_CASINOLOCATIONDET.CASINOLOC, D_CASINOLOCATIONDET.TBLAREA, D_CASINOLOCATIONDET.SiteID FROM D_CASINOLOCATIONDET) aa order by siteid asc, casinoloc asc, SctyCde asc, casinolocdetid desc --

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Lookup condition
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: CASINOLOC = IN_CasinoLocation AND TBLAREA = IN_TblArea AND SiteID = IN_SiteID

TARGET.DESCRIPTION:
Tracks the patron's responses to promotions, complementary items and other incentives promoted by the business. Essentially, a patron earning / redeeming points / comp / comp value at a point in time. This data capture will assist in determining, how much the promotions cost versus how much they benefit the business in terms of increased spend and/or visit frequency, whether any reduction in these (incentive amount or frequency of offer) has a negative impact on spend and / or visit frequency etc.
Grain is a single earning / redemption transaction / event with a patron earning / redeeming points / comp / comp value at a point in time.

MAPPLET.DESCRIPTION: Validates Promotion Transaction data according to business rules described in ETL Data Validation Requirements document. Creates a flat file with rejected records and a flat file with 'alert' records to be sent to the business for further investigation.
MAPPLET.NAME: mpl_Validate_PromotionTransaction

TRANSFORMFIELD.EXPRESSION: DECODE( TRUE --Transaction Date prior to Crown Club join Date , PromoTransDtTm< D_Patron_CrownClubJoinDt, '1100' --RDMD or EXPD record with DateTime less than ISSD Date , ( GenericAuditStsCde = 'RDMD' OR GenericAuditStsCde = 'EXPD' ) AND W_Promotion_IssuedDt > PromoTransDtTm, '1101' --Transactions with date prior to June 01 1994 , PromoTransDtTm < TO_DATE('19940601','YYYYMMDD'), '1102' --Internal Transfer Dollar Amount greater than Face Value Dollar Amount , IntTrsfrDlrAmt > FaceValDlrAmt, '1103' --Number of Points not Ratio*FaceValDlrAmt, only do check if Points and Dollar Amt is a positive value , NumPnts > 0 AND FaceValDlrAmt > 0 AND ROUND(NumPnts) != ROUND(FaceValDlrAmt * $$PointsRatio), '1104' --PromoLvl1 is Gift and PromoLvl4 is Purge and has a positive NumberOfPoints , UPPER(S_Promotion_Transaction_PromoLvl1) = 'GIFT' AND UPPER(S_Promotion_Transaction_PromoLvl4) = 'PURGE' AND NumPnts > 0, '1105' -- Comps with $ < 0. This used to be a reject - it still is for non-Comps , FaceValDlrAmt < 0 AND LegacyPromoTyp = 'CM', '1009' , NumPnts< 0 AND LegacyPromoTyp = 'CM', '1010' ----Added For Sydney since Department is not mandatory at IGT end ,S_Promotion_Transaction_PtyLocNum='900' and (ISNULL(S_Promotion_Transaction_DeptNum) or ISNULL(PromoDeptID)),'1003' --Lookup valid thresholds , TO_CHAR( :LKP.SHORTCUT_TO_LKP_W_PROMOTIONTHRESHOLDS( S_Promotion_Transaction_PromoLvl1 , S_Promotion_Transaction_PromoLvl2 , S_Promotion_Transaction_PromoLvl3 , S_Promotion_Transaction_PromoLvl4 , FaceValDlrAmt , SiteID ) ) )
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: v_ValidCde

TRANSFORMFIELD.EXPRESSION:
DECODE( TRUE --Promotion ID is NULL , INSTR($$SuppressErrorCodeList,'1001')=0 AND ISNULL(PromoID), '1001' --Patron ID is NULL , INSTR($$SuppressErrorCodeList,'1002')=0 AND ISNULL(PatronID), '1002' --Department ID is NULL , INSTR($$SuppressErrorCodeList,'1003')=0 AND ISNULL(PromoDeptID) and (v_Burswood_Flg or v_Melbourne_Flg) , '1003' --Casino Location Detail ID is NULL , INSTR($$SuppressErrorCodeList,'1004')=0 AND ISNULL(PromoTransLocID),'1004' --Hour ID is NULL , INSTR($$SuppressErrorCodeList,'1005')=0 AND ISNULL(PromoTransHrID),'1005' --Comment ID is NULL , INSTR($$SuppressErrorCodeList,'1006')=0 AND ISNULL(PromoCmtID),'1006' --LegacyPatronID not a positive 8 digit character , INSTR($$SuppressErrorCodeList,'1007')=0 AND ( ISNULL(LegacyPatronID) OR LegacyPatronID > 99999999 OR LegacyPatronID < 0 ), '1007' --Actioned Resource ID is NULL , INSTR($$SuppressErrorCodeList,'1008')=0 AND ISNULL(ActndResourceID), '1008'
--Face Value Dollar Amount less than 0 (Except for GF & CM for Melbourne) , INSTR($$SuppressErrorCodeList,'1009')=0 AND FaceValDlrAmt < 0 AND LegacyPromoTyp != 'CM' AND LegacyPromoTyp != 'GF' AND v_Melbourne_Flg , '1009'
--Face Value Dollar Amount less than 0 (Except for GF & CM and Promolvl1 in (COMPMEMB,CCLBNPNT) for Burswood) , INSTR($$SuppressErrorCodeList,'1009')=0 AND FaceValDlrAmt < 0 AND LegacyPromoTyp != 'CM' AND LegacyPromoTyp != 'GF' AND v_Burswood_Flg and UPPER(S_Promotion_Transaction_PromoLvl1)!='COMPMEMB' and UPPER(S_Promotion_Transaction_PromoLvl1)!='CCLBNPNT', '1009'
--Internal Transfer Dollar Amount is less than 0 (except Comps) , INSTR($$SuppressErrorCodeList,'1011')=0 AND IntTrsfrDlrAmt < 0 AND LegacyPromoTyp != 'CM' , '1011' --RDMD record without ISSD record , INSTR($$SuppressErrorCodeList,'1012')=0 AND GenericAuditStsCde= 'RDMD' AND ISNULL(W_Promotion_IssuedDt),'1012' --EXPD record without ISSD record , INSTR($$SuppressErrorCodeList,'1013')=0 AND GenericAuditStsCde = 'EXPD' AND ISNULL(W_Promotion_IssuedDt),'1013' --Number of Points less than 0. Do not perform validation where PromoLvl1 ='Gift' and PromoLvl4 is 'Prge'. , UPPER(S_Promotion_Transaction_PromoLvl1) = 'GIFT' AND UPPER(S_Promotion_Transaction_PromoLvl4) = 'PRGE', NULL , UPPER(S_Promotion_Transaction_PromoLvl1) = 'GIFT' AND UPPER(S_Promotion_Transaction_PromoLvl4) = 'ADJD', NULL , UPPER(S_Promotion_Transaction_PromoLvl1) = 'GIFT' AND UPPER(S_Promotion_Transaction_PromoLvl4) = 'MRGE', NULL , INSTR($$SuppressErrorCodeList,'1010')=0 AND NumPnts < 0 AND LegacyPromoTyp != 'CM', '1010' --Error PtyLocNum , ISNULL (SiteID), '10' , NULL)
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: v_ValidCde

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Sql Query
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: SELECT S_Promotion_Transaction.LegacyPatronID, S_Promotion_Transaction.DeptNum, S_Promotion_Transaction.CasinoLoc, S_Promotion_Transaction.TblArea, S_Promotion_Transaction.ActndResourceID, S_Promotion_Transaction.AuthEmpLicID, S_Promotion_Transaction.PromoTransDt, S_Promotion_Transaction.PromoTransTm, S_Promotion_Transaction.LegacyPromoTyp, S_Promotion_Transaction.LegacyPromoID, S_Promotion_Transaction.ProgNum, S_Promotion_Transaction.LegacyAuditStsCde, S_Promotion_Transaction.GenericAuditStsCde, S_Promotion_Transaction.PartRdmdFlg, S_Promotion_Transaction.CompletelyRdmdFlg, S_Promotion_Transaction.FaceValDlrAmt, S_Promotion_Transaction.IntTrsfrDlrAmt, S_Promotion_Transaction.NumPnts, S_Promotion_Transaction.ExpyDt, S_Promotion_Transaction.CmtDesc, S_Promotion_Transaction.PromoLvl1, S_Promotion_Transaction.PromoLvl2, S_Promotion_Transaction.PromoLvl3, S_Promotion_Transaction.PromoLvl4, S_Promotion_Transaction.PromoLvl5, S_Promotion_Transaction.PromoLvl5Desc, S_Promotion_Transaction.NumCredits, S_Promotion_Transaction.PtyLocNum, S_Promotion_Transaction.Qty, S_Promotion_Transaction.UnitVal, S_Promotion_Transaction.GeneratedbySysCde, S_Promotion_Transaction.LegacyCouponID, S_Promotion_Transaction.BillTo, S_Promotion_Transaction.Cost, S_Promotion_Transaction.Budget, S_Promotion_Transaction.CompType, W_Promotion.IssuedDt, W_Promotion.RdmdDt, W_Promotion.ExpiredDt, W_Promotion.DeletedDt, D_Comment.CmtID FROM S_Promotion_Transaction left outer join W_Promotion on S_Promotion_Transaction.LegacyPromoTyp = W_Promotion.LegacyPromoTyp AND S_Promotion_Transaction.LegacyPromoID = W_Promotion.LegacyPromoID AND W_Promotion.SiteId = $$SiteID left outer join D_Comment on S_Promotion_Transaction.LegacyPromoTyp = D_Comment.CmtTypCde AND ISNULL(S_Promotion_Transaction.CmtDesc, 'No Transaction Comment') = D_Comment.CmtDesc WHERE S_Promotion_Transaction.GenericAuditStsCde != 'DELE' AND S_Promotion_Transaction.PtyLocNum = $$Property_no ORDER BY S_Promotion_Transaction.LegacyPromoTyp , S_Promotion_Transaction.LegacyPromoID ,S_Promotion_Transaction.DeptNum , S_Promotion_Transaction.GenericAuditStsCde , convert(datetime, S_Promotion_Transaction.PromoTransDt, 103) DESC , S_Promotion_Transaction.PromoTransTm DESC

INSTANCE.DESCRIPTION: Compares current record to previous record. If LegacyPromotionID, LegacyPromotionType and GenericAuditStatusCode is the same then only keep the latest record. Variables are used to store the values of the previous record so that it can be compared to the current record.
INSTANCE.NAME: Exp_FlagDuplicates

INSTANCE.DESCRIPTION: Filters out records that has DeleteFlag = '1'
INSTANCE.NAME: Fil_FilterDuplicates

INSTANCE.DESCRIPTION: Join Statging table transactions to W_Promotion - where the transactions have already been loaded - to get Issued / Redeemed dates for validation. Join to D_Comment here because it is too big to use a Lookup.
INSTANCE.NAME: SQ_Get_Issd_Rdmd_Dates

INSTANCE.DESCRIPTION: Remove promotions with DeletedDt set to not null. This cannot be done in the source qualifier, because the left outer join to W_Promotion is created using Transact-SQL outer join syntax. A clause AND W_Promotion.DeletedDt IS NULL would run *before* the outer join, instead of after it. This means that the S_Promotion_Transaction row would still be picked up instead of being filtered.
INSTANCE.NAME: Fil_Remove_Deleted_Promotions

INSTANCE.DESCRIPTION: Splits data into different streams depending on whether the record is to be updated or inserted.
INSTANCE.NAME: Rtr_InsUpd

INSTANCE.DESCRIPTION: Translate the source ports into target ports, performing unconnected lookups to retrieve surrogate keys.
INSTANCE.NAME: Exp_TranslateTargetPorts

INSTANCE.DESCRIPTION:
Determine whether a record should be inserted, updated or deleted.
PromType--Status--Rule GF--ISSD--OneOnly CM--ISSD--OneOnly CM--RDMD--OneOnly CM--EXPD--OneOnly CP--ISSD--Many CP--RDMD--OneOnly CP--EXPD--OneOnly DP--ISSD--OneOnly DP--RDMD--Many DP--EXPD--OneOnly
For any of the OneOnly type transactions, if a record with the same LegacyPromotionID, Type, and Status has been processed either in the current file or on a previous day, then we will update the existing record. We shall assume that if the duplicate record is in the same file, then the first one will go through the NEW file, and the second through the UPD files. Variables are used to store the values of the previous record so that it can be compared to the current record.
INSTANCE.NAME: Exp_SetUpdInsFlag

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Lookup Sql Override
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: select aa.CASINOLOCDETID as CASINOLOCDETID, aa.CASINOLOC as CASINOLOC, aa.TBLAREA as TBLAREA, aa.SiteID as SiteID from ( SELECT D_CASINOLOCATIONDET.CASINOLOCDETID, case loctypcode when 'T' then 1 when 'S' then 1 when 'B' then 2 when 'C' then 2 when 'F' then 2 when 'O' then 2 when 'R' then 2 when('U') then 9 else 5 end as SctyCde, D_CASINOLOCATIONDET.CASINOLOC, D_CASINOLOCATIONDET.TBLAREA, D_CASINOLOCATIONDET.SiteID FROM D_CASINOLOCATIONDET) aa order by siteid asc, casinoloc asc, SctyCde asc, casinolocdetid desc --

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Lookup Sql Override
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: SELECT x.PATRONID as PATRONID , x.CROWNCLUBJOINDT as CROWNCLUBJOINDT , x.LEGACYPATRONID as LEGACYPATRONID , x.BEGEFFDT as BEGEFFDT , x.ENDEFFDT as ENDEFFDT ,x.SiteId as SiteID FROM ( select distinct a.*,b.patronid,b.CROWNCLUBJOINDT,b.begeffdt,b.endeffdt from ( select distinct s.legacypatronid,s.promotransdt, s.PtyLocNum, case when s.PtyLocNum='400' then 1 when s.PtyLocNum='600' then 2 else 3 end case as siteid from S_Promotion_Transaction s where s.GenericAuditStsCde != 'DELE' ) a left outer join uvw_Lkp_Patron b on convert(integer,a.legacypatronid) =b.legacypatronid and convert(datetime,a.promotransdt,103) >= b.begeffdt and convert(datetime,a.promotransdt,103) < b.endeffdt and a.siteid=b.siteid ) x

SHORTCUT.COMMENTS:
Tracks the patron's responses to promotions, complementary items and other incentives promoted by the business. Essentially, a patron earning / redeeming points / comp / comp value at a point in time. This data capture will assist in determining, how much the promotions cost versus how much they benefit the business in terms of increased spend and/or visit frequency, whether any reduction in these (incentive amount or frequency of offer) has a negative impact on spend and / or visit frequency etc.
Grain is a single earning / redemption transaction / event with a patron earning / redeeming points / comp / comp value at a point in time.
SHORTCUT.NAME: Shortcut_To_F_Promotion_Transaction
